    "body": "### Problem\n\nwhen setting `vim.opt.winborder`, using a string such as this: `\",,, ,,,, \"` simply causes this error:\n```\nE5113: Lua chunk: vim/_core/options.lua:0: E474: Invalid argument\n```\n\nthis means that you can't have a solid color border without using `vim.opt.winborder = \"solid\"`, and you also can't have it only on some sides of the floating window.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe expectation for the example above would be a border style where the border only appears on the left and right of floating windows, and those borders simply being a simple background color. this effectively adds a bit of padding to only the left and right sides. the `vim.opt.winborder = \"solid\"` option is very similar to this, but doing `vim.opt.winborder = \" , , , , , , , \"` also produces this error so i assume that the `\"solid\"` preset is some built-in magic :)",
